The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 November is 6,988 (808.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 November, there were 858 new confirmed cases (99.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 October, there were 818 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% ( 40 extra cases).
